AUDIO: 'that they can spend no matter what, you\'re going to create what\'s called a market distortion. And so a market distortion is where prices don\'t actually match supply and demand. Uh and the way that that shakes out is that say'

[14:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for instance you have uh you know Detroit just as an example and everyone ends up with you know $2,400 a month of UBI or even more. What UBI does is that uh instead of that area having some'

